<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,379,152,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">
I. 
<taxonomicName box="[177,379,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Brachymeriinae">Brachymeriinae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="254" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,222,391]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">
The genera included have been classified either in the 
<taxonomicName box="[805,939,222,247]" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Chalcidinae">Chalcidinae</taxonomicName>
(Bouček 1988a, 1992) or 
<taxonomicName box="[1257,1436,222,247]" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Brachymeriinae">Brachymeriinae</taxonomicName>
(Steffan 1951a). Phylogenetic studies (Wijesekara 1997; Heraty 
<emphasis box="[880,931,258,283]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">et al</emphasis>
. 2013; Cruaud 
<emphasis box="[1108,1158,258,283]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">et al</emphasis>
. 2016) mostly support a sister group relationship between the tribe Phasgonophorini, which includes the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sichel" authorityYear="1866" box="[1210,1324,295,318]" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" genus="Trigonura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1210,1324,295,318]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Trigonura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the Brachymeriini, whereas the Chalcidini merge on a separate node. Hence, it seems preferable to include 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1829" box="[151,297,366,391]" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" genus="Brachymeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,297,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Brachymeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sichel" authorityYear="1866" box="[351,465,367,390]" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" genus="Trigonura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[351,465,367,390]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Trigonura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, comprising the two tribes quoted above, in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[1125,1307,366,391]" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Brachymeriinae">Brachymeriinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
